{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation","step":0},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place garlic in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","step":1},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place a large sheet of baking paper (approx. 40 cm x 60 cm) on a work surface. Arrange rosemary sprigs on baking paper, then arrange 50 g bacon slices overlapping slightly. Place turkey leg on bacon and rub meat with chopped garlic. Season with ½ tsp salt and black pepper, then wrap turkey in the bacon and cover with remaining 100 g bacon slices. Drizzle with olive oil. Fold baking paper to form a parcel, twist ends tightly to retain the cooking juices and place parcel in Varoma dish.","step":2},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place water and remaining ½ tsp salt in mixing bowl. Set Varoma in position and steam <b>50 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","step":3},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Set Varoma aside. Insert simmering basket in mixing bowl and add potatoes to it. Set Varoma back in position and steam <b>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma and check that turkey leg is cooked. If necessary steam a further <b>3-10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> (for every 100 g additional weight of turkey leg, add approx. 3 minutes).","step":4},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Remove Varoma and carefully open parcel, reserving cooking juices. Transfer turkey leg to a serving dish and slice meat. Drizzle cooking juices over turkey slices and serve hot with potatoes.","step":5}],"usefulItems":"baking paper","id":"r150902","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-PXViqzj2Ba4\/XZQwFfJbdJI\/AAAAAAAAcio\/bf7NbtFglhsSUrTcDqqlb1jsdfYGl1yygCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_SsQdbVUh3bGV5gso.png","title":"Bacon-wrapped Turkey Leg with Potatoes","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"30 g garlic cloves"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"5 sprigs fresh rosemary"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"50 g bacon slices"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"800 g turkey leg, skinless, bone-in"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"3 pinches ground black pepper"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g bacon, sliced"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"20 g extra virgin olive oil (2 Tbsp)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1300 g water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"600 g potatoes, cut in pieces (4 cm)"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","2174 kJ \/ 520 kcal","51 g","26 g","23 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["<i>This dish is as festive as any roast, moist and flavourful, and easy to prepare. You can enjoy your guests’ company while it steams in the Varoma, and the clean-up after they leave is quick and simple.<\/i>","To make sure a few holes in the Varoma dish remain unobstructed for steam to circulate, you can place the butterfly whisk in the centre of the Varoma dish underneath the meat parcel to raise it off the bottom of the Varoma dish."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 40m","4 portions"]}